// STUB ONLY - local editor assistance
//
// Why this file exists:
// - Prisma VSCode extension validates a single file in isolation.
// - The shop plugin schema references models defined in other schema files
//   (for example `SysUser` in `prisma/schema/system.prisma`).
// - During isolated validation, those cross-file models are not visible,
//   which causes false errors like:
//   "Type \"SysUser\" is neither a built-in type..."
//
// How to use this file:
// - Keep only minimal placeholder models needed for IDE diagnostics.
// - Do not add datasource/generator blocks.
// - Do not add business fields, indexes, or constraints.
// - Do not import this file into runtime code.
//
// Build/DB behavior:
// - This file is NOT part of runtime schema assembly.
// - Final Prisma schema is generated from plugin source schema files and
//   written to `apps/yishan-api/prisma/schema/*.prisma`.
// - `db:prisma:sync` and `db:generate` must continue to succeed even if
//   this file is removed.
//
// Future microservice split:
// - These placeholders document cross-module dependencies.
// - When splitting services/databases, replace Prisma relations with
//   service-level references (e.g. `userId`) where needed.

datasource db {
  provider     = "mysql"
  relationMode = "prisma"
}
